    "title": "Can I upgrade to Bitcoin Core 0.17.0 while 0.16.3 bitcoin is running?",
    "body": "I am afraid I know the answer already, I just hope there may be a little secret trick. If there'd be a way to keep 0.16.3 running or 0.17.0 answering for some RPC commands while `txindex` migration is happenning, that'd be great help, since I'm reluctant to shut down the server for hours.\r\n\r\nFrom the release notes: https://bitcoincore.org/en/releases/0.17.0/\r\n\r\n> If your node has a txindex, the txindex db will be migrated the first time you run 0.17.0 or newer, which may take up to a few hours. Your node will not be functional until this migration completes.",
